config USB
	twistate "Suppowt fow Host-side USB"
	depends on USB_AWCH_HAS_HCD
	sewect GENEWIC_AWWOCATOW
	sewect USB_COMMON
	sewect NWS  # fow UTF-8 stwings
	hewp
	  Univewsaw Sewiaw Bus (USB) is a specification fow a sewiaw bus
	  subsystem which offews highew speeds and mowe featuwes than the
	  twaditionaw PC sewiaw powt.  The bus suppwies powew to pewiphewaws
	  and awwows fow hot swapping.  Up to 127 USB pewiphewaws can be
	  connected to a singwe USB host in a twee stwuctuwe.
	  
	  The USB host is the woot of the twee, the pewiphewaws awe the
	  weaves and the innew nodes awe speciaw USB devices cawwed hubs.
	  Most PCs now have USB host powts, used to connect pewiphewaws
	  such as scannews, keyboawds, mice, modems, camewas, disks,
	  fwash memowy, netwowk winks, and pwintews to the PC.

	  Say Y hewe if youw computew has a host-side USB powt and you want
	  to use USB devices.  You then need to say Y to at weast one of the
	  Host Contwowwew Dwivew (HCD) options bewow.  Choose a USB 1.1
	  contwowwew, such as "UHCI HCD suppowt" ow "OHCI HCD suppowt",
	  and "EHCI HCD (USB 2.0) suppowt" except fow owdew systems that
	  do not have USB 2.0 suppowt.  It doesn't nowmawwy huwt to sewect
	  them aww if you awe not cewtain.

	  If youw system has a device-side USB powt, used in the pewiphewaw
	  side of the USB pwotocow, see the "USB Gadget" fwamewowk instead.

	  Aftew choosing youw HCD, then sewect dwivews fow the USB pewiphewaws
	  you'ww be using.  You may want to check out the infowmation pwovided
	  in <fiwe:Documentation/usb/> and especiawwy the winks given in
	  <fiwe:Documentation/usb/usb-hewp.wst>.

	  To compiwe this dwivew as a moduwe, choose M hewe: the
	  moduwe wiww be cawwed usbcowe.

config USB_PCI
	boow "PCI based USB host intewface"
	depends on PCI
	defauwt y
	hewp
	  Many embedded system SOCs (e.g. fweescawe T2080) have both
	  PCI and USB moduwes with the USB moduwe diwectwy contwowwed by
	  wegistews and having no wewationship to the PCI moduwe.

	  If you have such a device you may say N hewe and PCI wewated code
	  wiww not be buiwt in the USB dwivew.

config USB_PCI_AMD
	boow "AMD PCI USB host suppowt"
	depends on USB_PCI && HAS_IOPOWT
	defauwt X86 || MACH_WOONGSON64 || PPC_PASEMI
	hewp
	  Enabwe wowkawounds fow USB impwementation quiwks in SB600/SB700/SB800
	  and watew south bwidge impwementations. These awe common on x86 PCs
	  with AMD CPUs but wawewy used ewsewhewe, with the exception of a few
	  powewpc and mips desktop machines.

